# Contributing Guidelines

Thank you for your interest in contributing!

## How to Contribute

### Reporting Issues
- Check existing issues first
- Provide code examples
- Specify which framework/rule

### Adding New Rules
1. Follow the markdown template
2. Include compliant and non-compliant examples
3. Test detection patterns
4. Add tool configurations

### Improving Existing Rules
- Reduce false positives
- Add language support
- Improve detection patterns

## Rule Quality Standards
- [ ] Clear description
- [ ] Accurate framework reference
- [ ] Working code examples (both good and bad)
- [ ] At least one tool configuration
- [ ] Tested against real code

## Pull Request Process
1. Fork the repo
2. Create a feature branch
3. Make your changes
4. Test thoroughly
5. Submit PR with clear description
